    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA313-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu tōḻi ciṟaippuṟamākat talaimakaṭkuc (ET: talaivikkuc) colluvāḷāyp puṉam aḻivu (ET: puṉamaṭi; C1: puṉamī) uraittuc ceṟippaṟivuṟīiyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante informed of confinement by talking about the ruin of the field as one speaking to HER when [HE] was behind the fence.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA313">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>          karuṅkāl vēṅkai nāḷuṟu putuppū</l>
<l>          poṉcey kammiyaṉ kaiviṉai kaṭuppat</l>
<l>          takaivaṉap puṟṟak kaṇṇi kaṭṭaḻit</l>
<l>          tolipal kūnta laṇipeṟap puṉaiik</l>
<l>          kaṇṭar kātal kaimmikak kaṭiyōṟ</l>
<l>          kiyāṅkā kuvaṅko ṟōḻi kāntaṭ</l>
<l>          kamaḻkulai yaviḻnta nayavaruñ cāraṟ</l>
<l>          kūtaḷa naṟumpoḻil pulampa vūrvayiṉ</l>
<l>          mīḷkuvam pōlat tōṉṟun tōṭupularn</l>
<l>          taruviyi ṉolitta lāṉāk</l>
<l>          koypataṅ koḷḷunāṅ kūun tiṉaiyē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>How will we be [attainable], friend,</l>
<l rend="indent">for the keen one of exceeding love, the one who saw [us]</l>
<l rend="indent2">decorating for adornment [our] sprouting many tresses,</l>
<l rend="indent3">ruining the tie of the chaplet that had befitting beauty,</l>
<l rend="indent3">resembling the handicraft of the artisan working with gold,</l>
<l rend="indent2">with the day-fresh new blossom of the black-trunked Vēṅkai?</l>
<l>The millet we shouted in is taking plucking-consistency,</l>
<l rend="indent3">endless the sounding of the waterfall,</l>
<l rend="indent">[its] leaves become dry, when it appears we seem to have to return</l>
<l rend="indent2">to the village, so that the fragrant Kūtaḷam grove will be lonely,</l>
<l rend="indent3">on the slope that evokes longing, where the fragrant bunches</l>
<l rend="indent4">of Malabar lilies have opened.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
